# Local-only signing / release config (copy to .env; .env is gitignored).

# --- Signing (scripts/smoke-test.sh) ---
# Developer ID Application cert in the keychain. Signing with this (plus hardened
# runtime) makes App Group widget data sharing and notifications work. Leave unset
# for ad-hoc signing (local runs only).
# DEVELOPER_ID="Developer ID Application: Your Name (TEAMID)"

# --- Notarisation (scripts/smoke-test.sh, distribution only) ---
# A notarytool keychain profile. Create it once with:
#   xcrun notarytool store-credentials "WhatBattery-notary" \
#     --apple-id you@example.com --team-id TEAMID --password <app-specific-password>
# With both DEVELOPER_ID and NOTARY_PROFILE set, the build notarises + staples.
# NOTARY_PROFILE="WhatBattery-notary"

# --- Homebrew cask bump (scripts/bump-cask.sh, scripts/release.sh) ---
# Path to a local clone of the homebrew-whatbattery tap. When set, the release
# updates the cask's version + sha256 after notarisation. Leave unset to skip.
# TAP_DIR="$HOME/Projects/personal/homebrew-whatbattery"

# Set to 1 to git-push the cask bump automatically. Default 0 = local commit only.
# CASK_AUTOPUSH=0
